div1.p:
Q. (to
William Roberts
) What may be the value of that print. - A. About forty-five shillings; that is the prime cost.

Q. Of course you can tell your own hand writing, and that of your sister's - whose hand writing is that. A. This is my sister's;
Sophia Smith
signed by me. (The receipt read.)

[


               The jury recommended the prisoner to mercy on account of her good character
            ].
